That avoids the 'closed while sending' because each subscriber knows when its data is ready. Here's a minimal implementation: ```rust
use tokio::sync::{Mpsc, Oneshot};
let (tx, rx) = Mpsc::unbounded();
tokio::spawn(async move { let _ = tx.send(42); });
await!(rx.recv().await); // actor logic here
